entry.lex: Alan Bean was born on March 15, 1932 in Wheeler, Texas and is American. He worked as a test pilot and was a member of Apollo 12, which was run by NASA. Bean is retired.

entry.lex: Retired American fighter pilot Buzz Aldrin, also known as Edwin E. Aldrin Jr., was born in Glen Ridge, New Jersey. He graduated from Massachusetts Institute of Technology in 1963 with a doctorate in Science and was a crew member on Apollo 11.

entry.lex: Fighter pilot Buzz Aldrin was born in Glen Ridge, New Jersey and graduated from Massachusetts Institute of Technology in 1963 with a doctorate in Science. He was a member of the Apollo 11 crew after being selected by NASA in 1963 with William Anders as a backup pilot on Apollo 11.

Buzz Aldrin was born in Glen Ridge, New Jersey. He graduated from MIT in 1963 with a doctorate in Science. He was a fighter pilot and began working for NASA in 1963. Aldrin was a member of Apollo 11, which was run by NASA and William Anders was the backup pilot.
